<script>
window.PROPEDGE_NEWS_PROXY = window.PROPEDGE_NEWS_PROXY || '/.netlify/functions/news?url=';
// ============================================================
// PropEdge — Fix 02: Team / Game / Player resolver
// ------------------------------------------------------------
// Problem: User asked the analyst about "San Antonio upcoming
// game" and got "CLE home vs DET" with Donovan Mitchell &
// Tobias Harris. Means team lookup ignored the user's query
// and the analyst pulled an unrelated stale game from cache.
//
// Approach:
//  - Build a normalized alias map covering NBA, NHL, MLB, NFL
//    (every PropEdge-supported league) keyed on city, full name,
//    nickname, abbr, and common variants ("San Antonio",
//    "Spurs", "SA", "SAS").
//  - resolveTeam(query, leagueHint?) returns the canonical
//    team object (id, league, abbr, fullName, city, nickname).
//  - resolveGameForTeam(teamId, schedule, opts) returns the
//    NEXT scheduled / live game for that team. Falls back to
//    the most recent completed game ONLY when explicitly asked.
//  - resolvePlayersForTeam(teamId, roster) returns the active
//    roster for that team — never returns players from another
//    team.
//
// Apply: drop this block into index.html INSIDE the existing
// <script> section that builds the analyst prompt, BEFORE the
// function that calls Ollama. Replace ad-hoc team/game lookup
// in the "Ask an Analyst" handler with calls to the helpers
// exposed on window.PropEdgeResolver.
// ============================================================

// -----------------------------------------------------------
// Alias data (GLOBAL). Keep this synced with the league rosters loaded
// by scraper-v13 / propEdge data layer. Aliases are lowercase,
// diacritic-stripped, punctuation-stripped.
